### Get All Stations
GET http://localhost:8080/api/stations

### Search for Trains
# Uses Station Codes (SBC, MYS, UBL etc.)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/search?from=SBC&to=MYS&date=2026-01-20

### View Seats
# Uses Train ID (not Number) and Coach Code
# Check the Train ID from Admin -> Trains if 1 does not exist.
GET http://localhost:8080/api/seats?trainId=1&date=2026-01-20&coach=S1

### Make a Booking
# NOTE: This endpoint requires Station IDs (Long), not Codes (String).
# You can find IDs from the GET /api/stations response.
# Ensure userId 1 exists (seeded by default).
POST http://localhost:8080/api/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "trainId": 1,
  "journeyDate": "2026-01-20",
  "sourceStationId": 1,
  "destStationId": 3,
  "coachType": "S1",
  "selectedSeats": [5, 6]
}

### Admin: Get All Trains
GET http://localhost:8080/api/admin/trains

### Admin: Add New Train
POST http://localhost:8080/api/admin/trains
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "trainNumber": "99999",
    "trainName": "Test Express",
    "totalSeatsPerCoach": 72
}

### Admin: Add Schedule (Stop)
# Requires valid Train and Station nested objects (or at least IDs if configured)
# Assuming IDs 1 exist for Train and Station.
POST http://localhost:8080/api/admin/schedules
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "train": { "trainId": 1 },
    "station": { "stationId": 3 },
    "arrivalTime": "10:00:00",
    "departureTime": "10:05:00",
    "stopSequence": 5,
    "distanceFromStartKm": 150
}

### Admin: Get Stats
GET http://localhost:8080/api/admin/stats

